<font color="#FF0000">I WONDER WHY...?</font><br>
<tt>Fri Jan 10 10:09:50 US/Eastern 1997
</tt><p>
<br>
 &lt;&lt; what bull shit.&gt;&gt;<br>
 This seems to be your favorite phrase.  Use it quite a bit.<br><br>
 &lt;&lt;Please hate my guts &gt;&gt;<br>
    I haven't read anywhere that anyone hated your guts, or any other part of you.  Some contempt yes, but hate---haven't seen it.  You're the doctor---what would you tell a patent that thought others hated them?<br><br>
&lt;&lt; I never ran. I stood my moral ground, which, yes, I think was higher than yours.&gt;&gt;<br>
   Ah---it must be wonderful to be so superior-and it didn't cost you a thing.  That student deferment allowed you to be &quot;courageous&quot; and safe at the same time.  Super.<br><br>
 &lt;&lt;I lived within and by the laws, something not all of you &quot;in country&quot; can claim.&gt;&gt;<br>
   The age old excuse of the coward and politicians--&quot;there's not one shred of evidence that......&quot;<br>
What does the comment about not all of us being able to claim this.  Of course not.  When you have over a million individuals involve you will have some bad apples, but what does that have to do with going or not going, if the war was just or unjust?  I said that I respected the ones wo protested and payed a price, but had only contemp for those who protested at no personal cost. I'll stand by that. By the way, no one spit on me---I was approached a couple of times, but I don't think I looked like someone it would be &quot;safe&quot; to spit on.  But your crowed did call my wife to tell her I'd been killed and telling her they hoped I'd be killed or maimed.<br>
 <br>
&lt;&lt; But please, don't give me this scenario about poor little villagers welcomming the &quot;beau geste&quot; of the big white god fathers (please overlook the racist tones), &gt;&gt;<br>
       What bothers me--and others here, is that you, a person who used the law to keep himself safe, totally ignore and denigrate the observations of those who were there.  I never said the villagers welcomed us all the time.  Those poor people were trying to stay alive and just wanted everyone to go away and leave them alone.  But, doctor, I was there, I did speak the language and I did talk to the privates, bar girls [yes talk] cab drivers, etc.  I did form impressions and while they may be wrong, they were gathered on the scene--not by reading some books writen by people who believed as i did. <br><br>
&lt;&lt; The historical facts regarding your &quot;po little villagers&quot; is quite different if you happen to be from Laos or Thailand, or other parts Asian. Please don't try and rewrite history in Christian Dogma either. &gt;&gt;<br>
     If you have a point here, I am afraid I missed it. <br><br>
&lt;&lt;What would have happen to all those dead, in Laos, Cambodia &gt;&gt;<br>
      The million and a half Cambodians were not killed because we were there.  They were killed because they didn't agree with their killers or were different---being able to read was justification for killing them and the point is we--not you--tried to prevent this, while you never, ever raised one word of protest.  You were safe, so who cares?  Such a high moral plane would gag a maggot.<br>
 &lt;&lt; Chatting with poor and starving people does not make one an expert in a culture that has been at war for over 100 years, and will probably say anything to you because of your nationality, Tanker.&gt;&gt;<br>
     No one said it does.  Just some observations from SOME ONE WHO WAS THERE.  Why do you run it down?  While it doesn' an expert make, they are honest observations and I made them.  Conclusions may be argued, but not the observations. <br><br>
&lt;&lt; Am I a racist, probably, &gt;&gt;<br>
   Well we do agree on something at last.<br><br>
&lt;&lt;but more likely, a realist. So the next time you want to make a grand gesture, or another &quot;beau geste&quot; send your own daughter or son, but I will be damned if you will get mine. &gt;&gt;<br>
    I simply will not apologize for trying to preserve the freedom of another country--even if they aren't white.  <br><br>
&lt;&lt;the question that worries me is where will misguided soldiers like you end up, which side will you be on when OUR country is at risk?&lt;&lt;<br>
    My father served the defense of this country---with his body--for 23 years and I did it for 32 years.  The most dangerous activity you ever engaged in was the possibility of getting your cloths dirty during a protest march.    &lt;&lt; what bull shit.&gt;&gt;<br>
